<main class="container">

<section class="article-hero">

<h1>Best Mac and Cheese Toppings</h1>

<p>
One of the easiest ways to upgrade mac and cheese is with the perfect topping.
From crunchy breadcrumbs to bacon and gourmet cheeses, toppings add texture,
flavor, and visual appeal to every bowl.
</p>

</section>

<section class="toppings-grid">

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Panko Breadcrumbs</h2>
<p>Light and crispy. Toss with butter and toast before adding to baked mac.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Crushed Crackers</h2>
<p>Classic topping made with Ritz or butter crackers.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Cheez-It Crumbs</h2>
<p>A fun upgrade that adds extra cheesy flavor and crunch.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Crispy Bacon</h2>
<p>Salty and smoky bacon takes mac and cheese to another level.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Fried Onions</h2>
<p>The same crunchy onions used in green bean casserole work great.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Parmesan + Herbs</h2>
<p>Fresh parsley, thyme, and parmesan create a gourmet finish.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Hot Sauce Drizzle</h2>
<p>A few drops of hot sauce balance the richness of cheese.</p>
</div>

<div class="topping-card">
<h2>Truffle Oil</h2>
<p>Just a small drizzle creates restaurant-style mac and cheese.</p>
</div>

</section>

<section class="article-section">

<h2>How to Make a Crispy Mac and Cheese Topping</h2>

<p>
Mix 1 cup breadcrumbs with 2 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle over
baked mac and cheese. Bake at 375°F until golden brown and crispy.
</p>

</section>

